metadata.name: operation 02 #75
metadata.description:
A further extrapolation of my operation 01 piece. Intentional errors are introduced. Per-view randomization is in the speed and size of the drawing of the arcs, and in the placement of the Voronoi points. Each viewing is unique, but each mint is also unique. 

The image draws in its entirety in about 10 seconds. After 20 seconds, it clears, randomizes the placement, and draws again. Full-screen capable.

Three traits describe each individual mint:

Color: There are nine different color palettes, with "Bubblegum" being a 20% likelihood, and all the others 10% likelihood.

Arc: This is the number of elements drawn around each point. There are three possible states, with 300 being a 10% likelihood, 3000 being a 20% likelihood, and 1500 being the default at 70%.

Resolution: This is the number of points in the Voronoi field. There are four candidates, with 2 being the least likely (10%), 3 and 4 having a 20% likelihood of occurring, and 5 being the most common at 50%.

Created in p5.js

metadata.name: operation 01 #35
metadata.description:
A Voronoi field is the basis, inspired by Jonathan Reynold's "voronoi noise" sketch (available here: https://openprocessing.org/sketch/1015631 ). This starting point is used to create an abstract image that keeps drawing infinitely. Per-view randomization is introduced in the speed and size of the drawing of the arcs, to create the chaos, and in the placement of the Voronoi points. This ensures each viewing is unique. Three traits describe each individual mint:

Color: There are nine different color palettes, with "Bay" being a 20% likelihood, and all the others 10% likelihood.

Arc: This is the number of elements drawn around each point. There are three possible states, with 50 being a 10% likelihood, 5000 being a 20% likelihood, and 500 being the default at 70%. 

Resolution: This is the number of points in the Voronoi field. There are four candidates, with 1 being the least likely (10%), 2 and 10 having a 20% likelihood of occurring, and 5 being the most common at 50%. 

Created in p5.js

metadata.name: broken laser printer #63
metadata.description:
If I have a super-power, it is this. When I get to within one meter of a printer or photocopier, they malfunction. Sometimes they jam, sometimes the sheets of paper get crumpled and torn, and other times the toner cartridges and drums get fouled and streaked.

This artwork is an abstract depiction of the state of printouts under the influence of my superpower. I always try to use my powers for good, but I am only human, and the result often has unintended side-effects.

Press "s" to save image.

Press "q" if you want to relieve stress caused by malfunctioning printers (does not affect the artwork in any way).

metadata.name: Digital Surface 1 #63
metadata.description:
The mechanics of Digital Surface is inspired by nature and the aesthetics by pixels. Digital Surface is an attempt to find an autonomous visual logic for a digital world made by machines.
The image is created one pixel after another, calculating the proceeding pixel based on the previous generations.
The color palettes are influenced by colors occurring in nature mixed with artificial man made colors that we see more today, aiming to look for new combinations that are pleasant to humans and natively digital.

Render time can be long. Once the image is completed, press "s" to save in a small size, "m" in a medium, "l" in a large, "x" in a xlarge and "w" to save with the size of the window.

Digital Surface is a 5 series project. Each Series is released singularly, the first being Digital Surface 1. The main differentiation for series 1 is that each image contains 2 colors.
This is Francesco Forcellini Studio's first NFT project broadening their field of work from physical to digital.

Built using p5js, published under CC-BY-NC-4.0 license.

Once the collection will be fully minted, the variations button will be disabled.

metadata.description:

- Colors (80% 2 colors, 20% 3+ colors, 4% 4+ colors, .8% 5 colors)
- Chaos (80% Low, 20% Medium+, 4% High)
- Storms (95% 1, 5% 2)

metadata.name: Surrounding Things - 質生塵 #122
metadata.description:
- 
Coordinating with Taipei: Art Salon 'Ties' with VolumeDAO, the auction will drop to 9.9 tezos on 12/15 at 11:00 AM (CET).

配合台北 VA Hub ‘Ties’ with VolumeDAO 藝術沙龍，拍賣將在12/15台北時間晚上7點下降至 9.9 tezos，一同共襄盛舉。

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This artwork is part of a series that Alvis currently exhibiton in Shanghai Film Art Center.

The powerful strokes of pixels stack up on the screen, revealing textures reminiscent of rocks sculpted by water and time, and structures resembling the muscles and bones of living organisms. Colors blend skillfully, creating the illusion of light and shadow, yet allowing one to feel the chill of moonlight and the lingering warmth of the setting sun.

The artist seems to have observed the shaping and destruction of the world with a detached perspective. It is a piece of art that appears to be the result of prolonged contemplation, profound insights, and strength.

metadata.name: Qoqnus #11
metadata.description:
Qoqnus

In ancient Greek: φοῖνιξ
In Arabic: Al-Anqa
In English: Phoenix

The sacred bird is a legend that is mentioned in Iranian mythology, Greek mythology, Egyptian mythology, and Chinese mythology.
It is said that he is a rare and lonely bird and does not mate or reproduce. But once every thousand years, it spreads its wings on a large pile of firewood and sings, and when it is excited by its song, it lights a fire with its beak, and by burning in the fire from its ashes, another phoenix is ​​born.
In many cultures, the phoenix is ​​considered a symbol of immortality, sacrifice and long life.

In this work, I tried to create bird-like shapes that are being formed and created by using a grid in the form of noise and with the shape of rectangles that have random length and width and get their color from the palettes. You can clearly see the wings or the bird's head in most of the exits
In fact, my idea is to depict the moment of resurrection and rebirth of the phoenix from the heart of the ashes, which rises to the sky.
the ash particles around this reborn bird are being scattered in the air and finally from At the heart of this re-creation, a beautiful and glorious phoenix comes into existence.

Made by p5.js

metadata.name: Allégories booléennes #372
metadata.description:
"Allégories booléennes" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

This work is a continuation of research around the intersections of shapes that I have been exploring for a while. I wonder about the way in which they make it possible to bring out new compositions from superpositions of shapes that could initially represent a real disorder.

Controls:
• "a": Play the animation
• "s": Export the image (default 2160 × 3840px PNG)
• "h": Change export settings to high resolution (then press "s" to export a 6480 ×11520px PNG)
• "m": Change export settings to medium resolution (then press "s" to export a 4320 × 7680px PNG)
• "n": Back to 2160 × 3840px

Artwork by Julien Espagnon, 2022.
